1. CONFIDENTIALITY

Definition:
Confidentiality means protecting information from unauthorized access.

Why it is Important:
It ensures that sensitive data is only available to authorized users.

Real-World Example:
Student records should only be accessible by authorized staff and students.

------------------------------------------------

2. INTEGRITY

Definition:
Integrity means ensuring that data remains accurate and unchanged.

Why it is Important:
It prevents unauthorized modification of information.

Real-World Example:
Exam results should not be altered by unauthorized individuals.

------------------------------------------------

3. AVAILABILITY

Definition:
Availability means ensuring that systems and data are accessible when needed.

Why it is Important:
Users must be able to access services without interruption.

Real-World Example:
The college website should remain accessible during admissions.

------------------------------------------------

